## § 4. Clap

Navigate to article, wait 2s.

🚨 **Hard cap: exactly 5 claps per article.** Medium allows up to 50 per user per article — 5 is enough to show appreciation without looking spammy. NEVER change this number. NEVER clap more than once per article (use commented_posts.txt or memory log to check).

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));
    const btn = document.querySelector('[data-testid="headerClapButton"]');
    if (!btn) return { error: 'clap button not found' };
    for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
      btn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('mousedown', { bubbles: true }));
      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 50));
      btn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('mouseup', { bubbles: true }));
      btn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true }));
      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
    }
    return { clapped: 5 };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```
🚨 mousedown→50ms→mouseup→click→500ms per clap. Without delays, rapid-fire triggers hold-to-clap (50 instead of 5).

